# STYLING
- Never write custom CSS or inline styles
- Never use arbitrary Tailwind values like w-[123px] or text-[14px]
- Use only CSS variables from globals.css for colors, spacing, radius
- Always use shadcn/ui components for UI — never create custom UI from scratch

# COMPONENTS
- Never modify files in /components/ui/ — these are shadcn/ui originals
- Before creating any new component, scan /components/ for a similar existing one
- Never duplicate components — always reuse existing ones
- All file names in kebab-case: user-card.tsx, stat-card.tsx, filters-bar.tsx
- Table rows must never duplicate — always use unique keys from real data
- Before creating any component → run npx shadcn@latest add [name] if it exists in shadcn/ui
- Never create inline custom styles for recurring UI patterns
- Always check lib/constants.ts for existing style constants before styling
- If pattern repeats 2+ times → create constant in lib/constants.ts and use it everywhere
- Never modify dialog.tsx to fix positioning — fix the parent layout instead

# FILE STRUCTURE
- Full pages → app/[page-name]/page.tsx
- Shared UI (sidebar, header, footer) → components/shared/
- Page-specific blocks → components/[page-name]/
- Complex logic (data fetching, filters, state) → hooks/use-[name].ts
- Extract to a hook only when logic is 20+ lines or reused on 2+ pages

# WHEN RECEIVING PAGE CODE
1. Identify shared elements (sidebar, header) → move to components/shared/
2. Identify page-specific blocks → move to components/[page-name]/
3. Keep page.tsx as layout only — just imports and composition
4. Add business logic as described in the task

# UI UPDATES
- When receiving updated UI code for existing component,
  update only the visual layer
- Never remove or replace existing business logic, hooks, or Supabase queries
- Merge new UI with existing logic, do not overwrite
- If user says "это код компонента [name] он был обновлён" →
  update only styles and structure, keep all logic intact

# UI INTERACTIVITY
- Radio buttons → always add selection state with useState
- Checkboxes in forms → always add checked state with useState
- Cards with radio/checkbox → clicking card = selecting it, highlight with ring-2 ring-primary
- Tabs → always add active tab state
- Accordion → always add open/close state
- Modal/Dialog → always add open state with trigger button
- Dropdown → always add open state
- After generating any component, check: are there interactive elements without state? Add it.

# LAYOUT QUALITY
- Full page layouts must always be min-h-screen
- Two-column auth layouts: each column exactly w-1/2, both min-h-screen
- Right decorative panel: flex-1 min-h-screen, no max-width restrictions
- Never use max-w on full-height columns
- Never let content dictate page height — page always fills viewport
- Decorative background shapes from Figma → recreate via CSS or inline SVG
- Cards with absolute positioning → preserve position (top/bottom/left/right)
- After generating any page, verify: no clipped columns, no missing backgrounds

# FONTS
- Fonts load automatically via get-css-fonts.ts which reads globals.css
- To change font → update --font-sans / --font-serif / --font-mono in :root in globals.css
- Never touch layout.tsx for font changes
- Fonts must exist in Google Fonts — verify before using

# ASSETS
- Before using any icon → check lucide-react first
- If icon exists in lucide-react → use component, never download
- If custom logo/icon not in lucide-react → export from Figma via API as SVG:
  1. Get file ID and node ID from Figma link
  2. Call Figma API: GET /v1/images/{file_id}?ids={node_id}&format=svg
  3. Save to /public/assets/[name].svg
- If banner/illustration/photo → export from Figma via API as PNG → /public/assets/
- Store all exported assets in /public/assets/
- Reference assets in code as /assets/[filename]
- Never hardcode external image URLs
- Figma access token is configured in Cursor MCP — use it directly

# DESIGN SYSTEM ONLY
- Never use browser default alerts, confirms, or prompts
- All notifications → use Toaster from @/components/ui/sonner
- All tooltips → use Tooltip from @/components/ui/tooltip
- All errors/validation → use Form from @/components/ui/form
- All modals → use Dialog from @/components/ui/dialog
- Modal/Dialog content background → always use variable popover (bg-popover); DialogContent already uses it by default
- All dropdowns → use DropdownMenu from @/components/ui/dropdown-menu
- Never use window.alert, window.confirm, console.log for user feedback
- Every user interaction must have feedback from design system components
- Status badges: match design exactly — outline in design → outline, filled → filled

# SUPABASE & DATABASE
- When connecting any feature to Supabase, always create a migration file
- Migration files → supabase/migrations/[timestamp]_[name].sql
- Migration must include: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS, RLS policies, indexes
- Never assume a table exists — always add IF NOT EXISTS
- After creating migration, add comment at top: "Run in Supabase SQL Editor before testing"

# MIGRATIONS
- Always create migration files in supabase/migrations/[timestamp]_[name].sql
- After every new migration, update supabase/migrations/setup.sql
- setup.sql must contain all migrations in order
- Always use CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS and ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS

# RELEASE MODE
- If CHANGELOG.md contains at least one release entry →
  automatically use release mode for all DB changes
- When user says "вывел в прод" →
  create new release entry in CHANGELOG.md with today's date
  and create supabase/migrations/release_N[number].sql
  with all migrations since previous release
- setup.sql never changes after first release

# RELEASE NAMING
- Release files: release_N1.sql, release_N2.sql, release_N3.sql
- CHANGELOG entries: Release N1, Release N2, Release N3
- Version increments by 1 on every prod deploy

# README
- Always keep README.md up to date
- Must contain: project setup, env variables, how to run locally, deploy instructions
- When adding new env variable → add to README immediately
- When adding new migration → update README deploy steps

# PIXEL PERFECT REVIEW
- After generating any page or component, always send a follow-up message:
  "Для pixel perfect сравнения — приложи скриншот из браузера
  или ссылку на фрейм в Figma. Сверю 1:1 и исправлю отличия."
- Never consider a component done without pixel perfect review
- During review → perform DEEP professional analysis, not surface check:
  1. Compare every spacing: padding, margin, gap — must match exactly
  2. Compare every font: size, weight, color, line-height
  3. Compare every color: background, border, text, icons
  4. Compare every component: size, variant, border-radius
  5. Compare layout: alignment, distribution, proportions
  6. Compare states: hover, active, disabled, empty
- Fix ALL differences found — never skip "minor" ones
- After first fix → compare again, repeat until 98%+ match
- Never say "практически совпадает" — always find and fix remaining differences
- NEVER change what already matches — only fix what differs
- Report every difference found as a numbered list before fixing

# CONSISTENCY
- Before creating any new component or page, scan existing components for style reference
- New components must match existing ones: same input styles, same spacing, same button sizes
- Never create components in isolation — always check what already exists first
- When creating similar components (forms, cards, tables) → open existing one and match exactly

# DASHBOARD CONCEPT
- All roles (admin, user, manager etc.) share the same dashboard shell
- Same layout, same sidebar structure, same menu behavior, same spacing
- Roles differ ONLY in: visible menu items, accessible pages, available blocks
- Never create separate dashboard layouts per role — one shell, role-based content
- Role-based visibility controlled via props or auth context, not separate components
- dashboard shell → app/dashboard/layout.tsx (shared for all roles)

# CLEANUP BEFORE RELEASE
- All demo components not related to project → mark with // TODO: REMOVE BEFORE RELEASE
- When user says "Удалить мусор" → delete all files and blocks with this comment
- Only run cleanup command before release, never during active development

# FILE STRUCTURE STRICT
- Never create (app) route groups unless explicitly asked
- Never create folders named after block slugs (dashboard-shell-05, application-shell-18 etc.)
- After importing any block → rename and move to correct location:
  - Shell/layout blocks → components/shared/
  - Page blocks → app/[page-name]/page.tsx
  - Sub-components of block → components/[page-name]/
- Never duplicate pages: if /dashboard exists → do not create second dashboard folder
- If block creates demo page → delete it, keep only the component
- Single source of truth for routes: app/ without route groups

# AFTER BLOCK IMPORT CLEANUP
- After installing any shadcn-studio block, always:
  1. Rename files from slug names to semantic names (dashboard-shell-05.tsx → dashboard-shell.tsx)
  2. Move components to correct folders per FILE STRUCTURE rules
  3. Delete demo/example pages created by the block
  4. Check for duplicate routes and remove them
  5. Update all imports to match new paths



# SHADCN STUDIO IMPORTS
- After installing any shadcn-studio block → immediately move all files to correct folders
- shared components → components/shared/
- page-specific → components/[page-name]/
- After moving all files → delete components/shadcn-studio/ folder completely including empty folders
- Never leave empty folders behind

# RESPONSIVE & LAYOUT
- Every page must be tested mentally for mobile, tablet, desktop before finishing
- Sidebar + main content → always use proper flex/grid, never overlap
- Main content must have correct margin/padding accounting for sidebar width
- Sidebar on mobile → always hidden by default, toggle via burger menu
- Never let sidebar overlap page content — use SidebarProvider with proper layout
- After generating any page with sidebar → verify: content not hidden behind sidebar

# COLORS FROM DESIGN
- Never guess or invent colors — always take exact colors from design reference
- When given screenshot or Figma → extract exact color values, do not approximate
- Semantic colors: success → green-600, warning → amber-600, error → red-600, info → blue-600
- Always use /10 opacity for badge backgrounds: bg-green-600/10 text-green-600
- When design shows outline → outline, filled → filled, never swap
- If color is unclear from design → ask, never assume

# TYPOGRAPHY IN TABLES
- First meaningful column (name, title) → always font-semibold or font-medium
- Secondary columns (category, type) → text-muted-foreground normal weight
- Never change font weight from what design shows
- When design shows bold text → font-semibold, never omit

# COLORS STRICT
- NEVER use hardcoded hex colors anywhere in code
- ALWAYS use CSS variables from globals.css: text-foreground, text-muted-foreground, bg-primary etc.
- When design shows any color → find matching CSS variable in globals.css, use that
- If no matching variable exists → ask, never hardcode
- Table text: primary content → text-foreground, secondary → text-muted-foreground
- globals.css tokens are synced with Figma — always use tokens, hex values are redundant
- When Figma shows #0A0A0A → this equals text-foreground, use text-foreground
- Never extract raw hex from design when token exists

# COMPONENT RECOGNITION
- When given a design screenshot → identify ALL UI components before writing code
- Never render a component as plain text or span if a design system component exists
- Badge → always Badge component, never span
- Button → always Button component, never div or a
- Input → always Input component, never plain input
- Before coding any element → ask: "does shadcn/ui have a component for this?"
- If yes → use it, never create custom HTML equivalent

# LOCALIZATION
- All UI text by default in Russian
- Labels, placeholders, buttons, tooltips, empty states → always Russian
- Date formats → русская локаль через date-fns/locale/ru
- Never use English text in UI unless it's a proper noun or brand name

# COMPONENT SIZING
- Always match component size to design reference exactly
- Button sizes: sm=h-8, default=h-9, lg=h-10 — pick by visual size in design
- Never upsize components when design shows small variant
- text-muted-foreground is grey, text-foreground is near-black — never confuse them
- When design shows dark/black text → text-foreground, never text-muted-foreground
- When in doubt about size → use default, never go larger than design shows

# DESIGN ACCURACY FROM SCREENSHOT
- When given any screenshot → before coding, analyze:
  1. Font sizes: heading, body, secondary text — map to text-sm/base/lg/xl/2xl
  2. Spacing: gaps between elements — map to gap-2/4/6/8/12
  3. Padding: inner spacing of containers — map to p-4/6/8/12
  4. Component sizes: buttons, inputs, badges — map to sm/default/lg
- Never guess — extract from screenshot before writing a single line
- Font size mapping: ~12px→text-xs, ~14px→text-sm, ~16px→text-base, ~18px→text-lg, ~20px→text-xl
- Spacing mapping: ~8px→gap-2, ~16px→gap-4, ~24px→gap-6, ~32px→gap-8
- When design shows large padding → never compress, preserve breathing room

# DROPDOWN & MENU HOVER STATES
- Dropdown menu items hover → rounded-md, never full-width flat highlight
- DropdownMenuItem hover must respect border-radius from design system
- Never override default shadcn/ui hover styles on menu items
- Menu items with icons → icon + text aligned with gap-2, icon text-muted-foreground
- Submenu indicator → ChevronRight icon, right-aligned

# BADGE SHAPE RULE
- Badge с числом → rounded-full
- Badge с текстом → согласно дизайн системе проекта

# DRY PRINCIPLE
- Before creating any new modal, form, page → scan project for similar components
- If new component differs only in title, button text, or data → use mode/type prop in existing component
- Pattern: one component + mode prop instead of two separate components
- Examples: add/edit modal → one component, create/update form → one component, view/edit page → one component
- Never duplicate structure — one component, different modes via props